Of course not. Much faster to type<p><pre><code>    UPDATE users SET email = username || '@facebook.com';
</code></pre>
Then let the users sort out the exceptions.

Putting the data argument second is nice when combined with currying. For example:<p><pre><code>  var bigNumbers = Udon.curry(Udon.filter)(function (number) {
      return number > 5;
  });
  bigNumbers([3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9]);  // [9]
  bigNumbers([2, 7, 1, 8, 2, 8]);  // [7, 8, 8]</code></pre>
